# Protected paths — single source of truth for the repo's agent guardrails.
#
# Consumed by: the git hooks (.githooks/), the CI `policy-guard` job, the Claude
# PreToolUse adapter (.claude/hooks/), and the CODEOWNERS generator. Editing any
# path matched here is a deliberate, reviewed act — not routine work.
#
# Format, one rule per line:   <glob>  |  <owner>  |  <reason>
#   - glob: gitignore-style; `**` spans directories, `*` stays within a segment.
#   - owner: GitHub handle that must review changes (flows into CODEOWNERS).
#   - reason: why this is load-bearing.
# Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# Deliberately a flat list, not YAML: the enforcers are zero-dependency POSIX
# shell, so the policy must parse without a YAML library. See ADR 0010.

tests/Harness/**          | @MgCohen | Test harness: the enforcement engine (ParityGuard, Rule, TestTypes).
tests/Meta/**             | @MgCohen | Meta tests that police the test taxonomy and parity.
tests/**/Rulebook/**      | @MgCohen | Rulebooks: the guarantees each test type proves.
.github/**                | @MgCohen | CI, CODEOWNERS, and repo workflow config — the server-side backstop.
.githooks/**              | @MgCohen | Local git-hook enforcers.
governance/**             | @MgCohen | The policy itself and its enforcers — cannot be quietly weakened.
design/adr/**             | @MgCohen | Architecture Decision Records — frozen history, not living docs.
.claude/settings.json     | @MgCohen | Claude harness config, incl. the PreToolUse guard — cannot disable its own guard.
CLAUDE.md                 | @MgCohen | Agent operating instructions for this repo.
Directory.Build.props     | @MgCohen | Solution-wide build config (nullable, warnings-as-errors, net10).
.editorconfig             | @MgCohen | Mechanical style rules.
ABox.slnx                 | @MgCohen | The one unified solution definition.
